title: Massac County's Girls Golf Team Wins 13th Straight Regional Title
text:
Massac County's Girls Golf Team Wins 13th Straight Regional Title Tools 
Story Created: Oct 7, 2015 at 5:17 PM   7, 2015 at 11:01 PM CDT 
ANNA -- Anna-Jonesboro hosted a girls 1A golf regional at Union County Country Club on Wednesday. 
Massac County won its 13th straight title with a score of 350. Herrin finished in second place with a 367, and Carterville captured third with a score of 368. 
Carterville's Avery Rea finished as medalist with a score of 79. Herrin's Macey Mooneyham claimed second with an 81. There was a three way tie for third place between Massac County's Millie Lawson, Sydney Boyd, and Herrin's Maegan Klinger. All three girls finished with an 86. 
For full results of the A-J Regional, click here: ihsa.org/data/gog/1winner183537.htm 
Also, the Mt. Carmel girls golf regional took place on Wednesday. Mt. Carmel finished in first place as a team with a score of 328. Pinckneyville captured second place with a score of 361. Nashville finished in third place with a 383. 
Mt. Carmel's Abbey Leighty was medalist with a 73. 
For full results of the Mt. Carmel Regional, click here: ihsa.org/data/gog/1winner183535.htm 
In 2A, no area teams advanced out of the O'Fallon Regional, but four individuals did. 
For full results of the O'Fallon Regional, click here: ihsa.org/data/gog/2winner183495.htm
